cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper presents a novel tracking framework that utilises convolutional networks for object tracking and recognition. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of pre-trained networks and inter-supervised learning to improve the tracking performance. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper presents an intelligent tracking system that can recognise the category of the tracked object. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with tracking objects in videos. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of tracking for robotic applications.
